is unreliable.

32:46.781 --> 32:48.447
Because when you tell a story,

32:48.449 --> 32:49.814
there's always an
essential distance

32:49.816 --> 32:51.716
between the story
itself and the telling

32:51.718 --> 32:53.218
of said story, right?

32:53.220 --> 32:57.822
So, therefore, every story
that has ever been told

32:57.824 --> 32:59.992
has an unreliable narrator.

32:59.994 --> 33:02.028
The only truly reliable
narrator would be

33:02.030 --> 33:04.263
someone hypothetically
telling a story that unfolds

33:04.265 --> 33:06.064
before our very eyes, which
is obviously impossible.

33:06.066 --> 33:08.567
So, what does that tell us?

33:08.569 --> 33:11.236
That the only truly
reliable narrator

33:11.238 --> 33:14.339
is life itself.

33:14.341 --> 33:19.077
But life itself is also a
completely unreliable narrator

33:19.079 --> 33:21.379
because it is
constantly misdirecting

33:21.381 --> 33:23.382
and misleading us and
taking us on this journey

33:23.384 --> 33:25.551
